Here’s a concise tutorial to help you get started with Datawrapper, a user-friendly tool for creating interactive charts, maps, and tables.

🧰 Datawrapper Tutorial: Creating Your First Chart
🎯 Goal:
Create a bar chart to visualize sample data using Datawrapper.

✅ Step 1: Create a Free Account
Visit https://www.datawrapper.de.

Click "Sign up" and create a free account using your email or Google login.

✅ Step 2: Prepare Your Data
Use a spreadsheet format like this:

Category	Value
Apples	30
Bananas	45
Cherries	25
Make sure:

The first row contains headers.

The data is clean—no empty rows or merged cells.

✅ Step 3: Upload Data to Datawrapper
After logging in, click “Create a chart.”

Choose “Chart” (you can explore “Map” or “Table” later).

Paste your data directly or upload it as a CSV/XLSX file.

Click “Proceed” when your data looks good.

✅ Step 4: Choose Your Chart Type
Select the appropriate chart type from the gallery (e.g., Bar Chart).

Preview how your data appears in different formats.

Click “Proceed” once you’ve selected the chart type.

✅ Step 5: Customize Design
Add a title, description, and source.

Adjust the colors, labels, axis formats, and tooltips using the "Visualize" tab.

Click through the Refine tab for advanced tweaks.

✅ Step 6: Publish & Share
Click “Publish & Embed”.

Copy the link to share or use the iframe embed code to insert into a website or WordPress page.

You can return to your chart anytime to edit and republish.

📝 Example Use Cases
Survey results

Library usage stats

Workshop attendance over time

Simple data comparisons (e.g., costs, time, impact)

